Modified to allow IAM Roles.
As per: https://github.com/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-cloud-aws
The plugin will default to using IAM Role credentials for authentication. These can be overridden by, in increasing order of precedence, system properties aws.accessKeyId and aws.secretKey, environment variables AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_KEY, or the elasticsearch config using cloud.aws.access_key and cloud.aws.secret_key

If no IAM role is used, and access and secret key are not set, the autodiscovery process will fail.

msg:
Merge pull request #12 from tony7126/master

Looks good--thank you for the update!

Revise the deployments example to be a bit more Ruby idiomatic

- If you already defined an attr_reader for an instance variable
``databases``, then you access it via ``databases``, too, skipping the
then-optional ``@``.
- You can also express the ``result = {}; so_something_with(result);
result``-pattern via ``Enumerable#each_with_object``.
- ``enum.map { |x| x.attrib }`` and ``enum.map(&:attrib)`` are
equivalent, but the latter is shorter.
- Don't use the return value of bang-methode prematurely: ``flatten!``,
for example, returns nil if no modifications were made!
Example bug using create timer and calling an activity.

Updated common-functions.sh

Updated common-functions.sh; modified the autoscaling_exit_standby() function to increment the ASG minimum size after taking an instance out of standby. Without this modification, the ASG minimum value will get decremented every time a CodeDeploy revision using these scripts is executed. If your ASG also includes downscaling/scale-in policies, this would cause instance terminations. This block resolves this issue.

Make sure (AZRebalance AlarmNotification ScheduledActions ReplaceUnhealthy) are suspended while deploying and resume only the ones suspended by the script.
Also abort if Launch process is disabled as it will not allow to return and instance from StandBy

Update README.md

- Added notice about suspended processes
- Fixed some Markdown style issues
- Fixed missing link to documentation
Fixed messaging if no previously suspended processes were found.
Added info about ELB_LIST options of _all_ and _any_ as well as style revamp.

Added a validation to avoid failing when it's the first deployment and deregister_from_elb.sh was not run on ApplicationStop
Made suspension of processes optional (default to false) and added clarification to README.md

Add Suspending/Resuming ASG Processes to ELBv2

The ELBv2 example scripts do not support suspending and resuming troublesome ASG
processes but the original ELB scripts do.

Update the ELBv2 `common_functions.sh` file to add this functionality.

 - Add a `HANDLE_PROCS` variable that denotes whether to suspend processes;
   defaults to false
 - Add a FLAGFILE implementation to keep track of which processes were suspended
   during the deploy and should be resumed
 - Update ASG decrementing to use the FLAGFILE instead of the single 'flag
   file'
 - Update the `README.md` to explain the ASG process suspension use case

msg: Added setup instructions to README.md and bucket name printing to fabfile.py
Updated setup instructions. New file: ECSLogo.zip with zipped contents of same directory.
Updated Docker file with more reliable build instructions.

Expanded support for ECS, ECR, and latest AWS API

Features added:

a) read credentials created by "aws configure" from ~/.aws/credentials
b) create s3 buckets in us-east-1 (boto does not understand location='us-east-1'; use '' instead)
c) use ECS clusters not named "default" (see config.py and ecs-worker-launcher/ecs-worker-launcher.js)
d) push and pull docker images in the ECR container service (specify DOCKERHUB_USER = '<USERID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com' and DOCKERHUB_REPO='latest')

msg:
Minor code improvements

For example, removing an unecessary `;` and adding some blank lines (to be
PEP-8 compliant).

Allow using custom tags in the security groups

Using a custom tag may be useful if we're already using the default
tags for other things. For example, if we're already using the tag
'Name' for cost allocation, or using the tag 'AutoUpdate' to update
packages via AWS Systems Manager.

To use a different (custom) tag, just set the corresponding environments
vars.

For example, you can set:

    TAG_NAME="X-Name"
    TAG_AUTO_UPDATE='X-AutoUpdate'
    TAG_PROTOCOL='X-Protocol'

And then tag your security groups using the tags `X-Name`, `X-AutoUpdate` and
`X-Protocol`.
Update incorrect AutoUpdate reference for tags

Use `logging` instead of `print`'s (#22)

* Use `logging` instead of `print`'s

Now, there's two kind of log levels (info and debug). Info is the
default, but you can set the debug mode via the `DEBUG` environment var.

Removing some extra spaces
Switched to urllib3 for requests as its bundled botocore (boto3)

msg:
Fixed bug#1. DNS record values being created on Route53 were not fully qualified.

This appears to be due a difference on how Route53 serves unqualified hosts names versus other DNS implementations. Actual reord sets between Micrsoft DNS, Bind and Route53 were identical but Route53 does not append the domain name to query result if the record is unqualified.

Updated the function to create fully qualified records for CNAME, MX, SRV and NS record types.

Added support for external domain resource records
If the resource record references a fully qualified DNS record then use that instead of appending the current DNS zone. This allows scenarios where a CNAME references another domain.
